00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:10,500
You know who else was married here?
Lesley Ann Martin.

736
00:47:10,600 --> 00:47:13,500
Herb Martin's daughter?
Well, forget it. This place is out.

737
00:47:13,600 --> 00:47:16,500
I'm not following
in Herb Martin's shoddy footsteps.

738
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:19,700
- I didn't see a stage either.
- Mother!
- Find something bigger.

739
00:47:19,750 --> 00:47:21,200
Eddie, what on Earth--

740
00:47:25,950 --> 00:47:27,200
What are you doing?

741
00:47:27,300 --> 00:47:28,800
Yeah, just a second.

742
00:47:32,900 --> 00:47:34,850
Good move, honey.

743
00:47:40,500 --> 00:47:42,950
From this valley

744
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:45,950
they say you are leavin'

745
00:47:46,050 --> 00:47:47,400
It's "going", honey.

746
00:47:47,450 --> 00:47:48,550
Whatever, darling.

747
00:47:48,650 --> 00:47:52,650
I shall miss your bright eyes

748
00:47:52,700 --> 00:47:56,000
And sweet smile...
smile smile smile

749
00:47:57,500 --> 00:48:01,900
I'm starting a nonprofit pediatric
foundation. I want Eddie to head it up.

750
00:48:02,000 --> 00:48:05,200
Can you imagine that, Eddie CEO
of a major medical foundation?

751
00:48:05,300 --> 00:48:07,250
He wants to
give up his patients?

752
00:48:07,300 --> 00:48:09,300
He does.
He just doesn't know it yet.

753
00:48:09,300 --> 00:48:11,600
He has a hard time
leaving people behind.

754
00:48:11,650 --> 00:48:13,600
Always do the right thing.

755
00:48:15,100 --> 00:48:18,900
I'm sure he doesn't always
do the right thing.

756
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:21,000
Just the something something

757
00:48:21,200 --> 00:48:25,050
Red River Valley

758
00:48:25,150 --> 00:48:27,550
Mom, would you please shut up!

759
00:48:29,200 --> 00:48:32,050
Whoa! Heel, boy!
Heel! Heel!

760
00:48:38,800 --> 00:48:40,650
Pull on the reins!

761
00:48:46,850 --> 00:48:48,900
Stop! Oh, God!

762
00:48:49,000 --> 00:48:51,300
Horsey! Horsey! Horsey!

763
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:52,650
Oh, God.

764
00:48:56,350 --> 00:48:57,800
Oh, God.

765
00:49:04,050 --> 00:49:05,450
Tree! Tree!

766
00:49:07,150 --> 00:49:08,550
Hang on, Mary!

767
00:49:08,650 --> 00:49:11,100
I got you! I got you!

768
00:49:12,200 --> 00:49:15,650
On the count of three.
One, two, three!

769
00:49:24,050 --> 00:49:25,600
You okay?

770
00:49:42,350 --> 00:49:45,350
Oh, my God.
You could've been killed.

771
00:49:45,400 --> 00:49:48,650
- You see it's important to learn how to ride a horse.
- Yeah.

772
00:49:48,700 --> 00:49:51,800
- Eddie, you're riding back with Mary.
- No, no, really.

773
00:49:51,900 --> 00:49:53,800
Don't let her out of your sight.

774
00:49:53,900 --> 00:49:56,900
And the good news is,
I have the wine!

775
00:50:01,350 --> 00:50:03,800
As I walked out on

776
00:50:03,900 --> 00:50:07,500
the streets of Laredo

777
00:50:19,050 --> 00:50:22,350
- Thank you for what you did.
- No problem.

778
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:26,400
You don't have to be
all smug about it.

779
00:50:28,750 --> 00:50:32,000
How about a quick recap here, Mary?

780
00:50:32,100 --> 00:50:34,750
You harpoon me for being engaged...

781
00:50:34,850 --> 00:50:40,700
when, in a zippy and unexpected twist,
you yourself turn out to have a fiance.

782
00:50:40,750 --> 00:50:43,400
Now you have the nerve
to call me smug?

783
00:50:43,500 --> 00:50:46,300
Come on, Mary.
What the hell is your problem?

784
00:50:46,350 --> 00:50:48,300
You're the one with the problem.

785
00:50:48,350 --> 00:50:50,500
I've been doing this a long time...

786
00:50:50,550 --> 00:50:53,800
and I can predict down to the week
how long a couple's going to last.

787
00:50:53,850 --> 00:50:58,050
Are you aware that Fran
has chosen teal for her bridesmaids?

788
00:50:58,050 --> 00:51:00,800
Teal, the color of gangrene.

789
00:51:00,850 --> 00:51:05,100
My last bride who chose teal
got her marriage annulled in 12 days.

790
00:51:05,150 --> 00:51:09,300
Oh, oh, and "I Honestly Love You"
as your wedding song?

791
00:51:09,400 --> 00:51:11,450
You might as well commit
matrimonial suicide right now.

792
00:51:12,950 --> 00:51:15,650
You want a confession in blood?
Huh? All right.

793
00:51:15,700 --> 00:51:18,950
That night at the movie,
I was attracted to you.

794
00:51:19,050 --> 00:51:21,950
I was. You caught me.
I admit it.

795
00:51:22,000 --> 00:51:26,250
I mean, let's see, maybe I was a little
unsure about the whole marriage thing.

796
00:51:26,350 --> 00:51:29,600
I don't know,
maybe I was just being a guy...

797
00:51:29,700 --> 00:51:32,200
and an opportunity presented itself.

798
00:51:32,300 --> 00:51:33,550
Bottom line?

799
00:51:33,650 --> 00:51:36,000
I never thought
I'd see you again.

800
00:51:36,050 --> 00:51:38,900
Bottom line?
Nothing happened.

801
00:51:40,300 --> 00:51:41,750
Bottom line?

802
00:51:41,850 --> 00:51:46,200
Now, more than ever,
I believe Fran is the one for me.

803
00:51:48,100 --> 00:51:49,150
So...

804
00:51:49,250 --> 00:51:52,800
I would say,
based on the evidence...

805
00:51:52,850 --> 00:51:57,200
all your theories on love sound more like
the rantings of a bitter, cynical woman.

806
00:52:01,400 --> 00:52:06,600
Once I walked out
on the streets of Laredo

807
00:52:06,700 --> 00:52:09,050
And Laredo walked out

808
00:52:09,100 --> 00:52:12,000
On the streets with me

809
00:52:33,250 --> 00:52:34,700
Excuse me.

810
00:52:34,800 --> 00:52:36,700
There's my good boy.

811
00:52:57,300 --> 00:52:59,300
What's going on?

812
00:52:59,350 --> 00:53:03,350
I am measuring you
for your wedding dress.

813
00:53:03,450 --> 00:53:06,650
Dad, I want my house key back.
Dad, dad, please.

814
00:53:08,100 --> 00:53:10,350
Where's that old wedding dress?

815
00:53:10,400 --> 00:53:13,450
Now we can finally
get rid of this.

816
00:53:13,550 --> 00:53:15,500
Dad, put that back!

817
00:53:15,600 --> 00:53:18,500
Hey, Mary,
what do you want on your bagel?

818
00:53:18,600 --> 00:53:21,300
No bagel. No wedding dress.
No wedding.

819
00:53:21,400 --> 00:53:22,300
No wedding?

820
00:53:23,650 --> 00:53:26,550
But Massimo said
you announced your engagement.

821
00:53:26,650 --> 00:53:28,500
I never said that.

822
00:53:28,600 --> 00:53:31,950
My God, this is like
the blind date that wouldn't end.

823
00:53:33,250 --> 00:53:34,450
He's right.

824
00:53:34,500 --> 00:53:38,550
You're frightened by
a mounting attraction for him.

825
00:53:38,600 --> 00:53:40,300
Oh, that's disgusting.

826
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:45,250
- I told you Mismo was full of crap.
- No Mismo! Massimo! Massimo!

827
00:53:45,300 --> 00:53:46,950
Please, go toast the bagel,
mind your own business.

828
00:53:47,050 --> 00:53:49,550
Yeah, I'll toast when I see fit.

829
00:53:49,600 --> 00:53:52,050
Mismo, Massimo
or any other kind of "mo."

830
00:53:52,100 --> 00:53:54,900
Dad, you cannot
push some guy at me.

831
00:53:54,950 --> 00:53:56,900
That's not how it works.

832
00:53:56,950 --> 00:53:58,900
Hey, you know that.
You had Ma.

833
00:53:58,950 --> 00:54:02,450
Yes, and I didn't meet her
until the day of our wedding.

834
00:54:02,550 --> 00:54:04,150
What are you talking about?

835
00:54:06,000 --> 00:54:09,300
Your mother and I
had an arranged marriage.

836
00:54:10,700 --> 00:54:12,800
An arranged marriage?

837
00:54:14,950 --> 00:54:18,000
We met on the day of our wedding.

838
00:54:18,100 --> 00:54:20,550
We couldn't even look at each other.

839
00:54:20,550 --> 00:54:23,050
I was in love
with another girl...

840
00:54:23,100 --> 00:54:27,400
and your mother
wanted nothing to do with me.

841
00:54:27,500 --> 00:54:31,450
She said I had big eyebrows
and a low IQ

842
00:54:32,500 --> 00:54:34,600
Anyway, one day...

843
00:54:34,650 --> 00:54:38,800
I got very sick
with scarlet fever...

844
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:42,700
and she stayed by my side.

845
00:54:42,800 --> 00:54:44,700
She took good care of me.

846
00:54:46,250 --> 00:54:48,700
For the first time...

847
00:54:48,800 --> 00:54:50,700
I appreciated her.

848
00:54:51,900 --> 00:54:54,850
Then the appreciation
grew to respect.

849
00:54:56,200 --> 00:54:58,600
Respect grew to like.

850
00:55:00,050 --> 00:55:03,300
Then like grew to love.

851
00:55:04,800 --> 00:55:07,750
A deeper love
than I could ever hope for.

852
00:55:11,250 --> 00:55:13,900
So give Massimo a chance.

853
00:55:15,450 --> 00:55:17,400
Maybe you don't like him now...

854
00:55:17,500 --> 00:55:20,700
but maybe
you might love him later.

855
00:55:21,800 --> 00:55:26,700
I should've told you about
your mother and I a long time ago.

856
00:55:26,750 --> 00:55:29,850
Maybe then you'd feel
differently about love.

857
00:55:33,950 --> 00:55:36,400
I don't feel anything about love.

858
00:55:40,850 --> 00:55:42,800
What do you think, Mary?

859
00:55:45,600 --> 00:55:47,550
Oh, the park's great.

860
00:55:48,650 --> 00:55:52,500
You guys would be the first. No one
else has ever been married here before.

861
00:55:57,350 --> 00:56:00,850
Well, we'd have to construct
the site from scratch...

862
00:56:00,900 --> 00:56:04,300
but at least you wouldn't
have to cut the guest list.

863
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:06,800
Dad would love it.

864
00:56:06,900 --> 00:56:09,400
And what about
the bride and groom-to-be?

865
00:56:09,450 --> 00:56:12,950
- I say, let's take it.
- I think we should keep looking.

866
00:56:12,950 --> 00:56:15,950
- Really?
- Maybe I should give you guys a minute.

867
00:56:17,300 --> 00:56:18,750
You don't like it?

868
00:56:21,550 --> 00:56:23,100
I don't know.

869
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:24,650
Come on.

870
00:56:29,200 --> 00:56:34,150
All right, if this is what you want,
then I'm-- I'm fine with it.

871
00:56:36,100 --> 00:56:38,500
Do you see why
I'm marrying this guy?

872
00:56:39,250 --> 00:56:42,150
Because he is so good to me.

873
00:56:42,250 --> 00:56:46,100
Yep, you two will have no problem
planning the wedding while I'm gone.

874
00:56:46,150 --> 00:56:48,650
- I beg your pardon?
- Just for a week.

875
00:56:48,700 --> 00:56:50,650
- Gone?
- I've got to fly back east.

876
00:56:50,700 --> 00:56:53,150
We're looking at buying out
a few of our manufacturers.

877
00:56:53,300 --> 00:56:57,250
- You know Fran, this is a really critical time.
- I know, that's why we shouldn't lose momentum, right?

878
00:56:57,350 --> 00:57:00,800
You guys will do a great job.
I trust you.

879
00:57:04,150 --> 00:57:06,550
Fran wants statues at the wedding.

880
00:57:06,650 --> 00:57:11,550
A well-chosen sculpture can help enhance
the tone and theme of the ceremony.

881
00:57:11,550 --> 00:57:13,550
Something like this could be nice.

882
00:57:13,600 --> 00:57:15,550
A little depressing, isn't it?

883
00:57:15,600 --> 00:57:18,400
No, it's wistful and romantic.

884
00:57:18,450 --> 00:57:19,800
Oh.

885
00:57:19,850 --> 00:57:21,300
Okay.

886
00:57:25,650 --> 00:57:29,250
I always pictured
a small wedding myself.

887
00:57:29,300 --> 00:57:31,800
Close friends and family.

888
00:57:31,900 --> 00:57:34,850
On the beach somewhere.
Cool, salty breeze.

889
00:57:37,200 --> 00:57:40,750
You know, the Aphrodite we passed
on the way in might be perfect.

890
00:57:40,850 --> 00:57:42,750
What about this guy?

891
00:57:42,850 --> 00:57:46,500
Well, this is all wrong for a wedding.
It's too menacing.

892
00:57:46,550 --> 00:57:49,100
Mary, I think you're wrong.

893
00:57:49,200 --> 00:57:52,100
He's not menacing.
He's masculine.

894
00:57:53,200 --> 00:57:54,950
He's the protector.

895
00:57:55,050 --> 00:57:57,100
- This man is strong.
- He's naked.

896
00:57:57,100 --> 00:57:58,400
This man is sturdy.

897
00:57:59,300 --> 00:58:01,150
Oh, my God.

898
00:58:01,250 --> 00:58:03,350
Pick him up
before somebody sees.

899
00:58:04,350 --> 00:58:05,750
You all right?

900
00:58:08,150 --> 00:58:11,150
- The man is heavy.
- Oh, my God, there's a guard coming.

901
00:58:12,900 --> 00:58:13,950
There.

902
00:58:14,950 --> 00:58:16,800
Oh, my God.

903
00:58:16,900 --> 00:58:18,750
You castrated him.

904
00:58:19,900 --> 00:58:21,550
Oh, no.

905
00:58:21,650 --> 00:58:23,250
The guard's coming this way.

906
00:58:23,350 --> 00:58:26,300
- I'm sorry, buddy.
- We gotta fix him.

907
00:58:27,250 --> 00:58:30,150
What do you got?
Oh, of course. Krazy Glue.

908
00:58:30,250 --> 00:58:34,500
Why didn't I bring Krazy Glue,
in case his pecker fell off?

909
00:58:34,550 --> 00:58:37,550
- All right, ready?
- Is it sticking?

910
00:58:37,600 --> 00:58:40,850
- You got it?
- Yeah, he's on. Oh, shit.

911
00:58:40,950 --> 00:58:43,250
Steve's stuck.
Steve's glued to his pecker.

912
00:58:43,350 --> 00:58:44,800
- Hi.
- Hi there.

913
00:58:44,850 --> 00:58:47,200
Sir, touching the statues
isn't permitted.

914
00:58:47,300 --> 00:58:48,700
Yes, sir.

915
00:58:48,800 --> 00:58:50,700
You're right.
It's limestone, not granite.

916
00:58:50,800 --> 00:58:53,700
We had a bet going.
She won.

917
00:58:53,800 --> 00:58:55,050
- Sir.
- Yeah?

918
00:58:55,150 --> 00:58:56,400
Your hand, sir.

919
00:59:01,100 --> 00:59:02,950
Yeah, my hand.

920
00:59:04,000 --> 00:59:06,250
Here it is.
You were right.

921
00:59:07,000 --> 00:59:08,600
A limestone penis.

922
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:11,850
You'd think he'd be bigger, huh?

923
00:59:14,800 --> 00:59:16,200
All right.

924
00:59:19,000 --> 00:59:19,900
Jesus.

925
00:59:21,100 --> 00:59:23,650
What else you got in that?

926
00:59:23,700 --> 00:59:25,300
My entire universe.

927
00:59:33,250 --> 00:59:34,650
- I'm sorry--
- I'm sorry--

928
00:59:34,750 --> 00:59:37,350
- I'm sorry. Go ahead.
- No, you go.

929
00:59:38,450 --> 00:59:40,700
I'm sorry about Napa.

930
00:59:42,250 --> 00:59:45,550
I didn't mean to call you
bitter and cynical. You're not bitter and cynical.

931
00:59:45,650 --> 00:59:49,900
And I'm sorry, what I said about
your marriage being doomed to fail.

932
00:59:51,850 --> 00:59:54,750
Well, I apologize for saying
you were just an opportunity.

933
00:59:56,050 --> 00:59:58,000
That was pretty ugly of me.

934
00:59:58,050 --> 01:00:02,100
And I was only half serious
about the teal bridesmaid thing.

935
01:00:03,300 --> 01:00:06,200
Well, at least I have
a 50-50 chance, right?

936
01:00:07,850 --> 01:00:10,800
You and Fran are gonna be
real happy together.

937
01:00:11,900 --> 01:00:14,850
So are you and Massimo.
It's gonna work.

938
01:00:14,900 --> 01:00:18,750
Yeah, well, um,
we're not engaged anymore.

939
01:00:20,250 --> 01:00:22,550
- Really?
- Really.

940
01:00:24,000 --> 01:00:26,000
- Are you okay with that?
- Yeah.

941
01:00:27,850 --> 01:00:30,750
It was more my dad
trying to get us together.

942
01:00:32,400 --> 01:00:34,600
What do you mean, why would he want to do that?

943
01:00:38,800 --> 01:00:41,800
Well, probably because
he was so happy with my mom.

944
01:00:57,200 --> 01:01:00,550
Fran said to go ahead and go forward
with the violet chocolate--

945
01:01:00,650 --> 01:01:03,300
- The chocolate one?
- The one that you suggested.

946
01:01:03,400 --> 01:01:05,700
Good. Then I'll
put in that order today.

947
01:01:05,750 --> 01:01:08,000
- How is Fran?
- She's good.

948
01:01:08,050 --> 01:01:11,750
She's making deals, kickin' butt.
You know, being Fran.

949
01:01:15,800 --> 01:01:17,950
Oh, nicely done.

950
01:01:21,350 --> 01:01:23,850
- Thank you, Mary.
- You're welcome.

951
01:01:23,850 --> 01:01:25,500
You wanna keep it?

952
01:01:26,700 --> 01:01:28,150
Sure.

953
01:01:34,100 --> 01:01:36,550
Wow, it's a nice day.

954
01:01:37,750 --> 01:01:40,700
I agree with you
about the small wedding.

955
01:01:42,100 --> 01:01:44,500
That's the way I'd do it too.

956
01:01:53,300 --> 01:01:54,750
Papa.

957
01:02:00,850 --> 01:02:03,700
How nice to see you.

958
01:02:04,800 --> 01:02:06,050
Where's my father?

959
01:02:06,100 --> 01:02:10,000
He's out buying the balloons
for Burt's birthday party.

960
01:02:10,750 --> 01:02:12,350
Tell him I was here.

961
01:02:12,400 --> 01:02:14,050
Wait, Mary.

962
01:02:14,800 --> 01:02:16,150
Are you mad with me?

963
01:02:16,200 --> 01:02:17,750
Yes...

964
01:02:17,800 --> 01:02:19,550
I'm mad at you.

965
01:02:19,650 --> 01:02:22,000
You told my father
we were engaged.

966
01:02:22,100 --> 01:02:25,000
He tried to measure me
for a wedding dress.

967
01:02:25,100 --> 01:02:28,050
What is the matter with you?
You never listen.

968
01:02:28,150 --> 01:02:31,800
Massimo, we are not going to
be together like that. Okay?

969
01:02:31,900 --> 01:02:35,400
- And why are you in my father's house?
- I am sorry. I will leave you alone.

970
01:02:36,500 --> 01:02:40,450
From now on, I will no longer bother you.
From now on, We will be just friends.

971
01:02:40,500 --> 01:02:43,450
Oh, you think we can be friends
just like that?

972
01:02:43,500 --> 01:02:46,850
I want to apologize
for any madness I caused you.

973
01:02:46,950 --> 01:02:48,300
Is this a trick?

974
01:02:48,350 --> 01:02:50,300
No tricks.
I'm very serious.

975
01:02:51,350 --> 01:02:53,850
I just want for us to be
buddy-buddy.

976
01:02:55,350 --> 01:02:57,800
I promise you.

977
01:02:59,650 --> 01:03:02,100
Do you have plans for dinner?

978
01:03:02,150 --> 01:03:05,950
No, as a friend, I want to
make for you a wonderful...

979
01:03:06,000 --> 01:03:07,950
American dish.

980
01:03:09,100 --> 01:03:10,750
Sit. I will start.

981
01:03:13,200 --> 01:03:15,750
That's your specialty?
Instant macaroni and cheese?

982
01:03:15,750 --> 01:03:18,200
It is a low-budget wonder.

983
01:03:18,250 --> 01:03:20,700
Already today,
I've eaten three boxes.

984
01:03:21,900 --> 01:03:24,500
Nothing like
a well-balanced diet.

985
01:03:24,800 --> 01:03:25,600
Gratie.

986
01:03:37,800 --> 01:03:41,550
- You remind me so much of your mother.
- You don't remember my mother.

987
01:03:41,650 --> 01:03:43,650
Yeah, I remember your mother.

988
01:03:44,700 --> 01:03:46,900
She had the same big smile...

989
01:03:46,950 --> 01:03:49,100
and the same dark hair.

990
01:03:49,200 --> 01:03:53,100
She had no nail on her little finger.
I don't remember why.

991
01:03:55,150 --> 01:03:58,700
Yeah, a brick fell on it from the kitchen,
when she was little. It never grew back.

992
01:03:58,750 --> 01:04:00,950
You see?
We have much history together.

993
01:04:01,000 --> 01:04:02,950
I guess we sort of do.

994
01:04:09,050 --> 01:04:11,950
You look like
you have much on your mind.

995
01:04:12,050 --> 01:04:13,450
Not at all.

996
01:04:14,600 --> 01:04:16,200
Well, I mean, we're friends...

997
01:04:16,250 --> 01:04:19,650
and friends listen when friends
are not feeling so good...

998
01:04:19,750 --> 01:04:21,850
so please to tell me.

999
01:04:25,500 --> 01:04:27,500
There's nothing to tell.

1000
01:04:27,600 --> 01:04:30,500
I thought I could control everything,
and I can't.

1001
01:04:31,650 --> 01:04:34,600
I met someone who I thought was--

1002
01:04:34,650 --> 01:04:36,150
Well, he's not.

1003
01:04:41,350 --> 01:04:44,550
Did you ever like somebody,
but the timing was off?

1004
01:04:45,750 --> 01:04:47,000
Way off?

1005
01:04:48,400 --> 01:04:51,800
You feel things that
you should not be feeling?

1006
01:04:54,750 --> 01:04:56,650
I'm not making any sense.

1007
01:04:58,750 --> 01:05:00,700
You make much sense.

1008
01:05:03,050 --> 01:05:06,400
You long for him
the way I long for you.

1009
01:05:10,150 --> 01:05:12,050
Massimo, I don't want you to think--

1010
01:05:12,150 --> 01:05:14,050
I want to tell you something.

1011
01:05:15,950 --> 01:05:18,550
You need to learn the patience.

1012
01:05:19,750 --> 01:05:21,700
I mean love can't always be perfect.

1013
01:05:21,750 --> 01:05:23,700
Love is just love.

1014
01:05:29,000 --> 01:05:30,950
My mom used to say that.

1015
01:05:31,000 --> 01:05:33,550
Your mother was a very wise woman.

1016
01:05:36,950 --> 01:05:38,300
Eat. Mangia.

1017
01:05:49,650 --> 01:05:54,800
So we'll start with camellias as a base,
that's what a friend and I discussed,
and anything else that jumps out at you.

1018
01:05:55,900 --> 01:05:58,300
- Let me know.
- Okay.

1019
01:05:58,400 --> 01:06:00,150
Roses.

1020
01:06:00,250 --> 01:06:01,650
Wreaths.

1021
01:06:01,750 --> 01:06:03,800
We don't need any more statues.

1022
01:06:05,000 --> 01:06:06,250
How about this beauty?

1023
01:06:06,300 --> 01:06:08,450
Interesting.

1024
01:06:08,500 --> 01:06:11,050
This is called a bleeding heart...

1025
01:06:11,150 --> 01:06:13,950
the official funeral flower
of Tibet.

1026
01:06:14,000 --> 01:06:16,200
I knew I'd be good at this.

1027
01:06:17,350 --> 01:06:19,200
I'll take
some Slit-My-Wrists-Susans...

1028
01:06:19,300 --> 01:06:21,200
and we'll be ready.

1029
01:06:24,700 --> 01:06:26,650
How'd you guys meet?

1030
01:06:26,700 --> 01:06:28,800
- Me and Fran?
- Yeah.

1031
01:06:28,900 --> 01:06:30,350
College.

1032
01:06:30,400 --> 01:06:32,400
She was in one of your classes?

1033
01:06:32,450 --> 01:06:34,550
No, she was a bookie, actually.

1034
01:06:34,650 --> 01:06:37,100
- Fran was a bookie?
- Yeah, she was a bookie.

1035
01:06:37,200 --> 01:06:39,100
She single-handedly established...

1036
01:06:39,200 --> 01:06:41,500
this underground gambling ring
at UC Berkeley...

1037
01:06:41,600 --> 01:06:44,300
took bets on every sporting event
that you could imagine, ran numbers...

1038
01:06:44,400 --> 01:06:47,300
and even hosted a Vegas night
at her sorority house.

1039
01:06:47,400 --> 01:06:49,800
- You're lying.
- No, that was Fran.

1040
01:06:49,900 --> 01:06:52,850
- Orchids? Does that work?
- Yeah, orchids would work.

1041
01:06:52,900 --> 01:06:54,200
Okay.

1042
01:06:54,300 --> 01:06:56,200
Yeah, she was the coolest.

1043
01:06:56,300 --> 01:06:59,450
I was the bookworm, she was
the wild child, and she picked me.

1044
01:07:01,250 --> 01:07:03,700
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

1045
01:07:05,050 --> 01:07:07,250
- How about cabbage?
- My God.

1046
01:07:08,900 --> 01:07:10,800
- What's the matter?
- Just hide me.

1047
01:07:10,900 --> 01:07:13,850
- Mary, what are you doing?
- Don't say my name!

1048
01:07:13,950 --> 01:07:15,450
Oh, my God.

1049
01:07:34,900 --> 01:07:36,050
You okay?

1050
01:07:36,100 --> 01:07:37,550
I found it.

1051
01:07:40,650 --> 01:07:43,050
Hi. How you doing?
I'm Steve Edison.

1052
01:07:43,100 --> 01:07:46,050
Keith Richmond.
My wife Wendy.

1053
01:07:46,100 --> 01:07:48,250
- Hi!
- Nice to meet you, Wendy.

1054
01:07:49,650 --> 01:07:52,000
So, how do you all know each other?

1055
01:07:52,900 --> 01:07:56,100
- It's a long story.
- Oh, let me tell it.

1056
01:07:56,200 --> 01:07:58,100
It's really a funny story.

1057
01:07:58,200 --> 01:07:59,600
See, Keith...

1058
01:07:59,700 --> 01:08:01,350
was my fiance.

1059
01:08:01,450 --> 01:08:04,900
And Wendy was
his high school girlfriend.

1060
01:08:04,950 --> 01:08:08,350
On the night of our rehearsal dinner,
I found them making out.

1061
01:08:10,500 --> 01:08:12,750
In my car.

1062
01:08:13,700 --> 01:08:16,050
I think that covers
all the high points.

1063
01:08:16,100 --> 01:08:18,050
Did I leave anything out?

1064
01:08:21,600 --> 01:08:23,550
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1065
01:08:26,800 --> 01:08:28,200
This home?

1066
01:08:30,500 --> 01:08:32,400
You wanna go up?

1067
01:08:43,800 --> 01:08:45,550
All right? You okay?

1068
01:08:45,600 --> 01:08:49,850
Jezebel was the only queen in the Bible
to be eaten by dogs.

1069
01:08:49,950 --> 01:08:52,900
- Did she fall down in the street?
- That's yours.

1070
01:08:54,500 --> 01:08:56,450
Hang on. Hang on.

1071
01:09:00,000 --> 01:09:03,600
- Mr. and Mrs. Wilfred Barber.
- No, it's not that one.

1072
01:09:05,350 --> 01:09:07,750
Nancy Pong.

1073
01:09:13,650 --> 01:09:15,150
Who is it?

1074
01:09:15,200 --> 01:09:17,250
Nancy Pong? 2C?

1075
01:09:17,350 --> 01:09:20,150
- Yes.
- Nancy, would you buzz us in, please?

1076
01:09:20,900 --> 01:09:23,250
It's Mary Fiore, 7H.

1077
01:09:23,300 --> 01:09:25,200
Who?

1078
01:09:25,250 --> 01:09:26,500
You don't know me.

1079
01:09:27,600 --> 01:09:29,500
We haven't met because...

1080
01:09:30,650 --> 01:09:33,250
I'm a control freak...

1081
01:09:33,250 --> 01:09:35,750
and I don't have time for people.

1082
01:09:37,500 --> 01:09:40,400
But if you ever need
to borrow a cup of sugar...

1083
01:09:41,600 --> 01:09:43,550
I can't help you...

1084
01:09:45,750 --> 01:09:48,300
'cause I don't have time to shop.

1085
01:09:58,700 --> 01:10:00,700
I wanna go home.

1086
01:10:01,950 --> 01:10:03,650
We are home.

1087
01:10:03,700 --> 01:10:06,350
We're just out on the porch.

1088
01:10:06,400 --> 01:10:07,850
All right?

1089
01:10:09,650 --> 01:10:11,550
He's married...

1090
01:10:13,050 --> 01:10:15,350
and they're gonna have a baby.

1091
01:10:17,950 --> 01:10:19,850
And he looked good.

1092
01:10:20,950 --> 01:10:22,250
No, he didn't.

1093
01:10:22,300 --> 01:10:24,800
- No, he really didn't.
- He did.

1094
01:10:28,350 --> 01:10:31,600
Hold it there, please. Thank you.
Here we go. We're in.

1095
01:10:31,650 --> 01:10:35,150
- I don't know him.
- I know, but this guy is gonna hold the door for us.

1096
01:10:35,200 --> 01:10:38,300
Come here. Here we go.
Stand up.

1097
01:10:38,400 --> 01:10:40,300
Hold that position. Here we go.

1098
01:10:40,400 --> 01:10:43,850
We got your beer, we got your purse,
we got you, we got your keys.

1099
01:10:43,950 --> 01:10:46,200
Hi there.
Here we go.

1100
01:10:46,250 --> 01:10:49,200
This is somebody that lives
in the same building. Thank you.

1101
01:10:49,200 --> 01:10:51,400
Are you Nancy Pong?

1102
01:10:52,750 --> 01:10:54,900
Okay, a little bit more.

1103
01:10:57,250 --> 01:10:59,200
A little fire.

1104
01:11:05,800 --> 01:11:07,750
Medium well.

1105
01:11:09,050 --> 01:11:11,950
You really don't think
he looked good?

1106
01:11:12,050 --> 01:11:14,450
Oh, no.
He looked old.

1107
01:11:14,550 --> 01:11:16,400
You know?

1108
01:11:16,400 --> 01:11:19,450
Unhappy and fat.
He put on a couple pounds.

1109
01:11:19,550 --> 01:11:20,950
Be quiet.

1110
01:11:26,950 --> 01:11:29,400
He said they were just friends...

1111
01:11:30,750 --> 01:11:32,850
but deep down, I knew better.

1112
01:11:40,150 --> 01:11:42,050
I was just a stand-in.

1113
01:11:43,600 --> 01:11:45,700
A poor man's Wendy.

1114
01:11:50,400 --> 01:11:53,050
Did you know that
she threw my bridal shower for me?

1115
01:11:53,100 --> 01:11:57,400
She even took time to freeze mint leaves
and raspberries in ice cubes.

1116
01:11:57,400 --> 01:12:00,550
That should've tipped me off
right there.

1117
01:12:00,650 --> 01:12:02,550
She was trying too hard.

1118
01:12:07,300 --> 01:12:08,700
Jerk.

1119
01:12:12,700 --> 01:12:15,750
It's a good thing I didn't marry him.

1120
01:12:22,000 --> 01:12:24,400
But most of the time I think...

1121
01:12:28,500 --> 01:12:31,100
I just wasn't enough.

1122
01:12:36,600 --> 01:12:39,000
No, no, no, you're wrong.

1123
01:12:45,200 --> 01:12:47,150
And another thing.

1124
01:12:49,750 --> 01:12:51,200
This Wendy...

1125
01:12:53,300 --> 01:12:56,500
she's nothing but a poor man's Mary.

1126
01:13:26,250 --> 01:13:27,650
It's getting late.

1127
01:13:33,300 --> 01:13:35,050
I'd better go.

1128
01:13:40,500 --> 01:13:42,450
I'll walk you to the door.

1129
01:13:42,500 --> 01:13:45,450
- That's all right. Stay there.
- No, it's okay.

1130
01:13:47,800 --> 01:13:50,200
- Wait.
- Take your time. You all right?

1131
01:13:56,700 --> 01:13:59,600
Thanks for tonight.
I know that I was a mess.

1132
01:13:59,700 --> 01:14:02,900
No, you weren't a mess.

1133
01:14:04,050 --> 01:14:05,500
A little bit.

1134
01:14:07,450 --> 01:14:08,550
Shut up.

1135
01:14:08,650 --> 01:14:11,200
- You gonna be okay?
- Yeah.

1136
01:14:11,300 --> 01:14:15,250
Two aspirin, a lot of water,
sleep, and a beer in the morning.

1137
01:14:15,300 --> 01:14:17,450
That's the cure.

1138
01:14:17,500 --> 01:14:19,700
- Good night, Mary.
- Good night.

1139
01:14:54,850 --> 01:14:57,000
Did you ever think about
that night in the park?

1140
01:14:57,100 --> 01:14:58,300
What?

1141
01:15:02,950 --> 01:15:04,900
I barely know you.

1142
01:15:06,250 --> 01:15:09,000
I don't know your dad's first name.

1143
01:15:09,050 --> 01:15:13,650
I don't know if you ever wore braces
or contacts or glasses.

1144
01:15:13,750 --> 01:15:16,650
I have no idea how you came to be
a wedding planner, Mary.

1145
01:15:22,550 --> 01:15:24,700
But I know
the curves of your face...

1146
01:15:27,850 --> 01:15:30,800
and I know every fleck of gold
in your eyes.

1147
01:15:36,050 --> 01:15:38,350
And I know that
that night in the park...

1148
01:15:41,800 --> 01:15:44,400
was the best time I've ever had.

1149
01:15:58,650 --> 01:16:00,350
Please say something.

1150
01:16:02,400 --> 01:16:05,000
I'm a magnet for unavailable men...

1151
01:16:08,600 --> 01:16:10,550
and I'm sick of it.

1152
01:16:15,050 --> 01:16:16,450
It's simple.

1153
01:16:18,800 --> 01:16:20,250
I know Fran.

1154
01:16:21,950 --> 01:16:23,450
I respect her.

1155
01:16:25,950 --> 01:16:27,400
And she loves you.

1156
01:16:32,150 --> 01:16:34,700
So, besides your tux measurements...

1157
01:16:36,700 --> 01:16:38,650
that's all I need to know.

1158
01:16:45,800 --> 01:16:47,500
Please go away.

1159
01:16:54,750 --> 01:16:56,550
Good night, Mary.

1160
01:17:18,250 --> 01:17:20,200
How do you word an invitation...

1161
01:17:20,250 --> 01:17:22,700
where both sets of parents
are paying for the wedding...

1162
01:17:22,750 --> 01:17:25,700
the groom is in the military,
about to receive a medical degree...

1163
01:17:25,750 --> 01:17:29,350
and the bride is a young widow whose father
recently had a sex-change operation...

1164
01:17:29,450 --> 01:17:32,900
and now goes by the name
Sugar Pie deSanto?

1165
01:17:33,000 --> 01:17:34,950
- Mary?
- What, what is it?

1166
01:17:35,000 --> 01:17:36,950
A little tense?

1167
01:17:37,000 --> 01:17:39,950
No... just terribly, terribly...

1168
01:17:40,050 --> 01:17:41,150
alert.

1169
01:17:45,850 --> 01:17:47,050
What's the matter?

1170
01:17:47,150 --> 01:17:49,200
I came back early.

1171
01:17:51,200 --> 01:17:54,050
Why?
I mean, is everything okay?

1172
01:17:54,150 --> 01:17:56,300
I've discovered something.

1173
01:17:58,000 --> 01:18:01,400
I've been blind.
I didn't want to see it.

1174
01:18:02,300 --> 01:18:04,850
I tried to ignore the signs.

1175
01:18:06,000 --> 01:18:08,100
I think you know
what I'm talking about.

1176
01:18:08,100 --> 01:18:11,850
Let me explain.
It's not what you think.

1177
01:18:11,900 --> 01:18:13,400
Yes, it is.

1178
01:18:15,150 --> 01:18:17,150
I can't go through with this wedding.

1179
01:18:18,900 --> 01:18:20,450
But, Fran--

1180
01:18:20,500 --> 01:18:23,900
I was in a meeting
talking about Boccolino mozzarella...

1181
01:18:23,950 --> 01:18:26,900
and it hit me
that this isn't going to work.

1182
01:18:28,250 --> 01:18:31,350
I can't stand the way
he chews on pen caps...

1183
01:18:31,450 --> 01:18:34,400
or the songs
that he sings in the shower.

1184
01:18:34,450 --> 01:18:40,050
It drives me nuts, the way that he hikes up his
left pant leg after he's eaten too much.

1185
01:18:41,450 --> 01:18:45,550
Is Eddie gonna be the last man
that I sleep with...

1186
01:18:45,600 --> 01:18:47,050
ever?

1187
01:18:49,000 --> 01:18:53,450
I've been with him so long, I don't
even know why we're together anymore.

1188
01:19:01,400 --> 01:19:02,700
Look at me.

1189
01:19:05,750 --> 01:19:07,700
You are exquisite.

1190
01:19:10,300 --> 01:19:11,500
You're timeless.

1191
01:19:13,650 --> 01:19:16,600
And you have the love
of a man named Steve.

1192
01:19:18,600 --> 01:19:24,050
A man who, while you were away having
meetings about mozzarella, said to me...

1193
01:19:24,150 --> 01:19:27,050
"I can't believe she picked me.

1194
01:19:29,750 --> 01:19:33,750
I can't believe I'm marrying the most
incredible woman I've ever met."

1195
01:19:40,150 --> 01:19:43,100
So that tells me
that this marriage of yours...

1196
01:19:44,500 --> 01:19:46,450
is not only gonna work...

1197
01:19:49,050 --> 01:19:51,200
it's gonna last forever.

1198
01:19:53,750 --> 01:19:54,900
Really?

1199
01:19:57,650 --> 01:19:58,850
Really.

1200
01:20:02,600 --> 01:20:04,050
Thank you.

1201
01:20:07,900 --> 01:20:09,850
Thank you, thank you.

1202
01:20:13,450 --> 01:20:15,750
For he's a jolly good fellow

1203
01:20:15,850 --> 01:20:18,650
For he's a jolly good fellow

1204
01:20:18,750 --> 01:20:21,300
- Which nobody can deny
- No one deny

1205
01:20:23,000 --> 01:20:25,900
Let me pray, let me pray.

1206
01:20:34,250 --> 01:20:37,250
Hope he didn't spit on the cake.

1207
01:20:37,250 --> 01:20:39,350
Come on.
Open up your presents.

1208
01:20:41,000 --> 01:20:44,550
No, no, please.
Everyone, I want to make some toast.

1209
01:20:47,000 --> 01:20:49,600
- Happy birthday, Burt.
- Salute.

1210
01:20:49,650 --> 01:20:53,850
Burt, Burt, buddy Burt.
Salvatore.

1211
01:20:53,900 --> 01:20:57,950
I want to thank Salvatore
for taking me into his life...

1212
01:20:58,050 --> 01:21:01,300
and introducing me
to all you wonderful people.

1213
01:21:05,500 --> 01:21:07,450
Hold on a moment.

1214
01:21:09,350 --> 01:21:11,250
Where is he going?

1215
01:21:41,000 --> 01:21:42,000
Mary...

1216
01:21:43,000 --> 01:21:47,650
I know I never done the right thing,
I never say the right thing...

1217
01:21:47,700 --> 01:21:49,800
and I act like a fool.

1218
01:21:53,050 --> 01:21:56,650
I know I say
we're just buddy-buddy friends...

1219
01:21:56,700 --> 01:21:59,700
but that would not be true
to my heart.

1220
01:22:01,350 --> 01:22:04,000
So I would ask you
this one question.

1221
01:22:04,050 --> 01:22:06,000
And if you answer no...

1222
01:22:08,050 --> 01:22:11,000
then I will leave you alone
once and for all.

1223
01:22:16,100 --> 01:22:18,600
Be my wife, Mary Fiore...

1224
01:22:20,350 --> 01:22:25,750
and I will take care of you
and be true to you...

1225
01:22:25,800 --> 01:22:29,450
and, like this house
I built for your dolls...

1226
01:22:29,550 --> 01:22:33,700
I will make sure you have
a strong roof over your head.

1227
01:22:33,750 --> 01:22:36,650
If your answer is yes...

1228
01:22:36,700 --> 01:22:40,250
then no one will ever love you
as much as I love you.

1229
01:22:42,000 --> 01:22:44,000
If your answer is yes...

1230
01:22:45,950 --> 01:22:49,400
you will make me
the happiest man on the Earth.

1231
01:25:37,050 --> 01:25:39,050
What would I have done
without you?

1232
01:25:39,050 --> 01:25:41,850
Hey, wedding woman,
you did some job.

1233
01:25:41,950 --> 01:25:45,250
My girl's gonna knock 'em dead.
Aren't you, sluggo?

1234
01:25:45,350 --> 01:25:49,250
Well, somebody stole my lucky mike.
I can't sing without my lucky mike.

1235
01:26:28,100 --> 01:26:29,700
What are you doing here?

1236
01:26:29,800 --> 01:26:32,900
You know it's bad luck
to see the bride before the wedding.

1237
01:26:36,150 --> 01:26:37,400
You look beautiful.

1238
01:26:38,250 --> 01:26:41,850
Go on. Get out of here.
We're starting any minute.

1239
01:26:41,950 --> 01:26:43,350
Come on.

1240
01:26:44,700 --> 01:26:47,800
- Let's take a walk.
- A walk?

1241
01:26:47,900 --> 01:26:50,250
A walk. Come on.

1242
01:26:50,350 --> 01:26:51,750
Come on.

1243
01:26:54,000 --> 01:26:56,600
No. What are you talking about?
You cannot give the whole wedding to me.

1244
01:26:56,700 --> 01:26:59,500
Everything is gonna be fine.
It's a no-brainer.

1245
01:26:59,550 --> 01:27:01,450
You can't do this.
Geri's out there!

1246
01:27:01,500 --> 01:27:04,500
So?
The whole commission is yours.

1247
01:27:06,200 --> 01:27:07,800
That's more money
than I make in a year.

1248
01:27:07,850 --> 01:27:11,750
Well then I guess that means we're gonna
have to go shopping next week.

1249
01:27:13,700 --> 01:27:16,700
I am completely confused.
Why are you doing this?

1250
01:27:18,250 --> 01:27:19,350
Because there's somewhere
I've gotta be.

1251
01:27:20,400 --> 01:27:23,300
Okay, we can talk
after the wedding.

1252
01:27:23,400 --> 01:27:25,400
Hang on a minute, Fran.

1253
01:27:27,800 --> 01:27:31,850
- Why do you wanna marry me?
- What?

1254
01:27:31,950 --> 01:27:34,100
That's one of the questions
I need answered.

1255
01:27:35,650 --> 01:27:37,300
Ok, Steve, you're scaring me.

1256
01:27:38,500 --> 01:27:39,950
You never call me Steve.

1257
01:27:40,700 --> 01:27:42,200
That's because you don't like it.

1258
01:27:44,550 --> 01:27:46,550
No, I never said I didn't like it.

1259
01:27:49,100 --> 01:27:52,100
- Okay, where is this going?
- Why do you wanna marry me?

1260
01:27:54,400 --> 01:27:56,400
Are you kidding me?

1261
01:27:56,450 --> 01:27:58,400
- Are you kidding me?
- No, I'm not.

1262
01:27:58,450 --> 01:28:02,100
You're trying to dump me
on the day of my wedding.

1263
01:28:02,150 --> 01:28:05,400
- I am not trying to dump you,
I just need to know your answer to that question.
- This is not happening to me.

1264
01:28:05,450 --> 01:28:07,950
- Franny, Franny.
- This is not-- don't "Franny" me!

1265
01:28:08,000 --> 01:28:10,600
Don't "Franny" me,
you selfish bastard!

1266
01:28:10,700 --> 01:28:13,500
Listen, the reasons we were together in college
don't hold up anymore.

1267
01:28:13,550 --> 01:28:15,500
We're different people now.

1268
01:28:15,550 --> 01:28:18,100
- And?
- And I think you know that.

1269
01:28:19,450 --> 01:28:21,350
Listen to me, Franny.

1270
01:28:21,450 --> 01:28:24,450
If you really love me,
I'll put this cummerbund on right now...

1271
01:28:24,550 --> 01:28:27,900
we'll walk up that hill
and go to the big tent and do it.

1272
01:28:27,950 --> 01:28:30,650
- You would do that?
- Yes, I would.

1273
01:28:33,300 --> 01:28:35,100
All those people.

1274
01:28:35,200 --> 01:28:37,750
You don't know half of 'em.

1275
01:28:39,350 --> 01:28:41,250
You and me.

1276
01:28:43,000 --> 01:28:44,400
Are you ready?

1277
01:28:47,650 --> 01:28:50,550
Yes. Yes, of course.

1278
01:28:54,000 --> 01:28:56,250
I just need a second.

1279
01:29:04,000 --> 01:29:05,400
Oh, God.

1280
01:29:24,000 --> 01:29:25,000
No...

1281
01:29:27,750 --> 01:29:30,700
I don't want to get married.

1282
01:30:22,500 --> 01:30:25,400
How did we let it get this far?

1283
01:30:26,900 --> 01:30:28,400
I don't know.

1284
01:30:29,650 --> 01:30:31,750
What are we gonna do?

1285
01:30:33,750 --> 01:30:36,750
Well, that's the beauty of it.

1286
01:30:36,850 --> 01:30:38,800
Whatever we want.

1287
01:30:41,900 --> 01:30:46,100
I haven't thought about
what I really want in so long.

1288
01:30:46,150 --> 01:30:47,600
Me neither.

1289
01:30:56,350 --> 01:30:58,850
There you go.

1290
01:31:04,550 --> 01:31:05,650
Okay.

1291
01:31:07,300 --> 01:31:09,450
Okay.

1292
01:31:20,200 --> 01:31:23,400
That is the bride.
Is that the bride?

1293
01:31:23,500 --> 01:31:25,300
Yes, it is.

1294
01:31:25,350 --> 01:31:27,300
Well, is she coming back?

1295
01:31:27,500 --> 01:31:27,900
No.

1296
01:31:31,650 --> 01:31:35,400
I think that all the blood is rushing
to my head and I'm gonna faint.

1297
01:31:35,450 --> 01:31:37,950
I'm gonna kill Mary
for leaving me all alone here.

1298
01:31:37,950 --> 01:31:39,950
- I don't know what to do.
- Penny, take a breath.

1299
01:31:40,050 --> 01:31:42,150
What are you talking about?

1300
01:31:42,250 --> 01:31:45,300
I'm talking about your wedding planner
leaving me here all alone...

1301
01:31:45,400 --> 01:31:47,550
to go to city hall
and get married.

1302
01:31:47,650 --> 01:31:49,550
Married?

1303
01:31:49,650 --> 01:31:52,300
- What? Mary's getting married?
- Yeah, married.

1304
01:31:52,400 --> 01:31:54,850
- You know, married?
- No, she can't get married.

1305
01:31:54,900 --> 01:31:56,850
- Married.
- Hey, hey, city hall.

1306
01:31:56,900 --> 01:32:00,350
Married, you know, like what
you're supposed to be doing.

1307
01:32:00,350 --> 01:32:03,100
Oh, that's-- Yeah.

1308
01:32:03,200 --> 01:32:07,500
That's great. Go. I'll tell everyone.
I'll tell Kathie Lee Gifford.

1309
01:32:13,450 --> 01:32:15,700
Beautiful.

1310
01:32:15,750 --> 01:32:17,300
Thanks.

1311
01:32:51,100 --> 01:32:53,200
Come on! Goddamn it.

1312
01:32:53,300 --> 01:32:55,700
Are you sure you
don't know a shortcut?

1313
01:32:55,800 --> 01:32:58,050
Take a shortcut somewhere?

1314
01:32:58,150 --> 01:33:00,050
- What do you expect me--
- Bullshit.

1315
01:33:00,150 --> 01:33:02,350
What are you doing?

1316
01:33:04,150 --> 01:33:06,850
Hold on the right. Hold!

1317
01:33:17,050 --> 01:33:20,300
We are gathered together
in the presence of these witnesses...

1318
01:33:20,400 --> 01:33:23,850
to join this man and this woman...

1319
01:33:23,900 --> 01:33:25,900
in matrimony.

1320
01:33:25,950 --> 01:33:28,750
This contract is not
to be taken lightly...

1321
01:33:28,800 --> 01:33:32,550
but thoughtfully and seriously...

1322
01:33:32,650 --> 01:33:35,000
with a deep realization...

1323
01:33:35,050 --> 01:33:39,550
of its obligations
and responsibilities.

1324
01:33:39,650 --> 01:33:41,600
If anyone can show just cause...

1325
01:33:41,700 --> 01:33:45,850
why these two should not
be joined together in matrimony...

1326
01:33:45,900 --> 01:33:48,450
then let him speak now
or forever...

1327
01:33:48,500 --> 01:33:50,450
hold his peace.

1328
01:33:55,800 --> 01:33:57,900
Fine.

1329
01:33:58,000 --> 01:34:00,600
- Then let us proceed.
- No.

1330
01:34:01,600 --> 01:34:04,250
- Thank God.
- Oh, hell, I object too.

1331
01:34:04,300 --> 01:34:05,600
What is going on here?

1332
01:34:08,000 --> 01:34:09,100
Here we go.

1333
01:34:13,450 --> 01:34:17,400
Maria, I look in your eyes
and it hurts my insides.

1334
01:34:17,450 --> 01:34:21,300
This is not what you want.
This is what I want.

1335
01:34:21,400 --> 01:34:23,050
Shame on me.

1336
01:34:23,100 --> 01:34:25,150
I'm so lucky
to have a father like you.

1337
01:34:27,150 --> 01:34:28,450
But you're right.

1338
01:34:29,900 --> 01:34:32,500
Love isn't like
some enchanted evening...

1339
01:34:33,750 --> 01:34:35,400
isn't a fairy tale...

1340
01:34:35,450 --> 01:34:37,950
or even love at first sight.

1341
01:34:39,300 --> 01:34:41,600
That isn't real life.

1342
01:34:44,650 --> 01:34:46,650
Massimo's a good man.

1343
01:34:46,700 --> 01:34:48,500
Don't worry, Papa.

1344
01:34:48,600 --> 01:34:51,350
I know what I'm doing.

1345
01:34:53,200 --> 01:34:55,250
I'm just all grown up now.

1346
01:35:01,850 --> 01:35:03,800
Okay.

1347
01:35:09,150 --> 01:35:10,950
Hey, that's the doc!

1348
01:35:11,000 --> 01:35:13,250
- Steve!
- Oh, yes.

1349
01:35:13,300 --> 01:35:15,500
- You know the doctor?
- Mary. Where's Mary?

1350
01:35:15,550 --> 01:35:17,500
I'm her father.
Who the hell are you?

1351
01:35:17,550 --> 01:35:19,750
- He's the doctor.
- I'm Steve, the doctor.

1352
01:35:19,800 --> 01:35:22,250
- I'm in love with your daughter.
- You are the one?

1353
01:35:22,300 --> 01:35:25,050
- What the hell is going on?
- I'm sorry, but I am.

1354
01:35:25,150 --> 01:35:27,800
- What about Fran?
- Fran and I did not get married.

1355
01:35:27,850 --> 01:35:29,800
That's been happening a lot today.

1356
01:35:29,850 --> 01:35:31,550
Whoa. You didn't get married?

1357
01:35:31,600 --> 01:35:35,150
We're not married. I am not the one.
You are the one, Steve.

1358
01:35:35,250 --> 01:35:37,600
And you didn't get married?
She's not married?

1359
01:35:37,650 --> 01:35:41,200
She does not love me.
She loves-- She loves you, Steve.

1360
01:35:42,800 --> 01:35:46,950
I could never forgive myself if ever
I got in the way of Mary's true love.

1361
01:35:47,000 --> 01:35:49,350
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm Steve.

1362
01:35:49,450 --> 01:35:50,750
He's Steve. He's the one.

1363
01:35:50,800 --> 01:35:52,750
I'm the doctor.
I'm in love with Mary.

1364
01:35:52,800 --> 01:35:54,750
Wait a minute!
Hold the phone.

1365
01:35:54,850 --> 01:35:58,500
You mean to tell me,
you love her and she loves you...

1366
01:35:58,600 --> 01:36:00,600
and neither of you
got married today?

1367
01:36:00,700 --> 01:36:02,350
That's what I'm saying.

1368
01:36:02,400 --> 01:36:05,450
Then what the hell are you
standing around talking to us for?

1369
01:36:05,550 --> 01:36:08,750
I don't know. Where is she?
Where is Mary? Somebody take me to Mary.

1370
01:36:08,800 --> 01:36:10,300
I take you. Come on.

1371
01:36:10,350 --> 01:36:12,550
- I like him.
- He's a doctor.

1372
01:36:23,200 --> 01:36:25,250
Congratulations!

1373
01:36:25,350 --> 01:36:26,700
Fabulous!

1374
01:36:26,750 --> 01:36:28,700
Good for you!

1375
01:36:30,500 --> 01:36:33,850
- Congratulations!
- Go, go. Thank you.

1376
01:36:56,600 --> 01:36:58,550
Thank you, Massimo!

1377
01:36:58,650 --> 01:37:00,750
You better be good to her!

1378
01:37:00,850 --> 01:37:03,650
I still do more chin-ups than you!

1379
01:37:31,550 --> 01:37:34,500
Why are you only eating
the brown ones?

1380
01:37:43,650 --> 01:37:46,550
Because someone once said that...

1381
01:37:46,650 --> 01:37:50,600
they had less artificial coloring
because chocolate's already brown.

1382
01:37:56,050 --> 01:37:58,150
And it kind of stayed with me.

1383
01:38:04,150 --> 01:38:06,000
You kind of stayed with me.

1384
01:38:15,400 --> 01:38:16,850
Where's Fran?

1385
01:38:17,900 --> 01:38:20,650
She's in Tahiti...

1386
01:38:20,750 --> 01:38:22,650
on our honeymoon.

1387
01:38:25,550 --> 01:38:27,150
We didn't get married.

1388
01:38:32,000 --> 01:38:33,100
Because?

1389
01:38:35,650 --> 01:38:38,900
Because she needs to
find her own life.

1390
01:38:44,750 --> 01:38:46,650
And I--

1391
01:38:49,400 --> 01:38:50,800
You what?

1392
01:38:54,100 --> 01:38:55,650
What does Steve want?

1393
01:38:56,800 --> 01:38:58,400
I want to dance...

1394
01:39:02,450 --> 01:39:04,350
with you.

